p: A total of 273 blood samples were collected from 273 healthy or asymptomatic individuals in the suburb of Nanning City (22.8170° N, 108.3665° E), Guangxi Province, China, in March 2019. All individuals were native of Nanning City without oversea experience with age distribution from 20 to 57 and gender ratio (male:female) 1.37:1. The study was reviewed and approved by the ethics committees of Wuhan University. Written informed consent was obtained from each person. Plasma samples were collected using 5ml BD Vacutainer Barricor plasma blood collection tubes. Plasma was immediately stored at –80°C.
